I’m honored to have been the first in my family to go to college. I thought I knew what career I wanted to pursue going in, but the journey allowed me to discover what I was actually passionate about. 

My initial interest in law started with my family experiences revolving around immigration. My aspiration to become a lawyer doesn’t end with just helping those in the same position as my family members, but to educate myself on the laws of our immigration system as well as where they stem from. 

My passion in politics and lawmaking fully took root after the 2016 election and since then, I have been researching how the law affects our day-to-day lives and how we can prevent injustices caused by inconsistencies in the law. 

Because of my interest in social justice, I majored in Sociology while minoring in Legal Studies. The different courses I took for my major sparked inspirations of what other fields of law I may want to practice in the near future such as Criminal Defense and Civil Rights. 

As I stand here today with my family’s sacrifices, their pride on my back, and my own goals to achieve, I plan on bringing  them nothing but honor. I hope that I will already have made a difference in the world with my passion, discipline, and education by the time I finish law school.

My family and myself lost everything July 31 due to a brand new AC exploding which caused the house to catch fire. Not only that we suffered fire damage we also had intensive water damage. We lost our cat as well. The tenants in our home personal belonging along with ours were destroyed in the fire. We lost everything on the evening of July 30. I just feel like July 2023 has been the worst month of my life.All of my equipment in my house was destroyed not because of the fire, but by water damage from the fire fighters. The cause of the fire is from a brand new window air conditioner unit that exploded on the first floor. We are currently living out of hotel rooms until we figure out whats next.  In order for me to get back to shooting again, I had to max out my credit card today to purchase a new computer, a monitor, docking station, graphic keyboard, mouse, a new screen tablet because I have an obligation of uploading my clients photos and editing them from the photoshoots I had on July 30th. We are strong and very independent we do not like to seek help or owing anyone but we need help. Home Insurance advised us that we will not be back in our house for 6 month to a year! SMHI created a special package on my site to assist my family and myself to get back on our feet sooner than later. You will be able to leave a tip in addition to the shoot price. You will be able to schedule shoots up until December 2023. I appreciate everyone who called me, DM me and pulled up on me. This is a very hard time for all of us.  Continue to keep us  in your prayers.

If you would like to send support without a photoshoot you can 
zelle - 347-696-5797
cash App - $Reekshotit
Apple Pay - 718-759-7649

We are appreciative of anything that you are able to send.

Presentations matter! If you’re set to party, you should be set for your shoot. A photoshoot is an interview for magazines, castings, etc. Look the part – you wouldn’t go to an interview looking like that. 💄👠
